    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-22T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-22T06:00:00-05:00" n="657"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.6363/418: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1941-11-22T14:00:00+03:00">November 22, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 23—3:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1964. Embassy’s 1961, November 21, 6 p.m. Vyshinski received me last night
                    immediately after he had seen the British Ambassador. I handed to him an <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> containing a paraphrase of the statement <pb
                        facs="0671" n="659" xml:id="pg_659"/> contained in the Department’s
                    instruction No. 1103, September 30, 7 p.m. This morning I conveyed orally the
                    further information that the Government of the United States would be disposed
                    to lend its good offices to prevail upon other oil producing nations to adopt a
                    similar policy.</p>
                <p>Vyshinski stated that he would bring the matter to the attention of his
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
